<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861231-0032 </DOCNO><HL> Times Mirror CompletesSale of Graphic Controls</HL><DD> 12/31/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TMCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> LOS ANGELES  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Times Mirror Co. said it completed the previously announced sale, valued at about $146 million, of its Graphic Controls Corp. unit in a leveraged buyout.    The unit was purchased by a new company formed by members of the unit's management and Brentwood Associates, an investment firm based here. Graphic Controls makes recording charts, marking systems, disposable medical products and coated imaging papers. Times Mirror is a publishing, paper products, broadcasting and cable television concern.    As previously reported, Times Mirror said the investors agreed to pay $80 million and to make additional payments totaling $41 million over the next two years. Times Mirror said it also would receive 6% preferred stock and 6% convertible preferred stock in the new company, with a total face value of $25 million. </TEXT></DOC>